# Command jit

## What does this command do:

Jira CLI for ticket lookup, detailed issue inspection, sprint views, and creating or editing issues from the terminal.

## Installed from

Dependencies: Rust toolchain (rustup + cargo). Install Rust first before running `cargo install jit-cli`.

For Fedora install using:
  curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y && source ~/.cargo/env
  cargo install jit-cli

For Raspberry Pi install using:
  curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y && source ~/.cargo/env
  cargo install jit-cli

For Mac install using:
  brew install rust
  cargo install jit-cli

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.cargo/bin/jit
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.cargo/bin/jit
For Mac run: ~/.cargo/bin/jit

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/cesarferreira/jit

## Command options

jit [OPTIONS] [TICKET] [COMMAND]

# Arguments
  [TICKET]    JIRA issue key (e.g., RW-1931) or URL (e.g., https://company.atlassian.net/browse/RW-1931)

# Commands
  create      Create a new Jira issue without sprint assignment (lands in backlog on scrum boards)
  edit        Edit an existing Jira ticket's core fields, including Task issues
  help        Print help for this command or a subcommand

# Options
      --json                           Output in JSON format
      --text                           Output as plain text: "KEY: Summary"
      --my-tickets                     Display your current sprint tickets in a table (default when no ticket given)
      --show                           Show detailed ticket info in table format
      --include-description            Include ticket description in detailed output
      --include-comments               Include ticket comments in detailed output
      --include-prs                    Include linked GitHub pull requests
      --full                           Include description, comments, PRs, and metadata
      --comments-limit <N>             Max comments to show (default: 5)
      --all-comments                   Show all comments (overrides --comments-limit)
      --since <YYYY-MM-DD>             Only include comments on or after this date
      --limit <N>                      Max tickets to retrieve (default: 10)
      --config-file <PATH>             Path to a custom config.toml file
  -h, --help                           Print help
  -V, --version                        Print version

# Examples
  jit RW-1931                          Show ticket summary
  jit --show RW-1931                   Show ticket details in table format
  jit --show --full RW-1931            Full details: description, comments, PRs, metadata
  jit --text RW-1931                   Single-line output: "RW-1931: Summary"
  jit --json RW-1931                   Machine-readable JSON output
  jit --my-tickets                     List your current sprint tickets
  jit create --project RW --summary "Fix login bug"          Create backlog issue
  jit create --current-sprint --project RW --summary "..."   Create issue in active sprint
  jit edit RW-1931 --summary "Updated summary"               Edit ticket fields
